The paper deals with the detection of internet filtering and censorship, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of principle component analysis and anomaly detection, which are techniques commonly used in data science and machine learning (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of global usage statistics from the Tor Project, which is a network anonymity tool, indicating a possible connection to the field of cryptography (cs.CY). The paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which could fall under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a new technique for identifying anomalous behavior, which could be of interest to the data science community (cs.DS).
